'''Oblee''' were three-armed sapients indigenous to [[Oblis]], although originally from the [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]].<ref name="LFC">''[[Living Force Campaign Guide]]''</ref>

Each Oblee had four [[Eye/Legends|eyes]], in two rows. The [[Color/Legends|color]] of each row could vary, as was the case with well-known Oblee [[Nirama]].<ref name="LFC" /> In cases of little sleep, the Oblee would show wrinkles under all of their eyes.<ref name="MW">{{LivingForce|Between the Worlds: MidWorld}}</ref>

Some members of the [[Species/Legends|species]] found the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] artifact known as the [[Darkstaff]]. The device eventually destroyed their homeworld, leaving the Oblee survivors adrift in the galaxy as spirit creatures that were referred to as '''shadow lurkers'''. They would sometimes try to interact with the physical world by sucking the life out of [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] beings and inhabiting their bodies.<ref name="Recursion">{{LivingForce|Belted In: Recursion}}</ref>

The Oblee had spread their DNA throughout [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] and eventually one called Nirama was born, believing that he was the only member of his species in existence.<ref name="Recursion" />

Common Oblee names included Azbedal, Flef, Kiffel, Nirama, and Ronorra.<ref name="Oblee" />

